Before I started skating, I basically wore uniforms or workout clothes for 90% of my entire life…that’s not an exaggeration. I’m still finding and creating my own sense of style, but loving the process. When I say skating changed my life, I mean it. It’s helped me discover who I truly am and gives me the confidence to express myself. I still feel myself holding back, but I’m looking forward to breaking though some of these walls next year 😆. 
.

This year I will be hosting a travel retreat! 🌍🛼*Link in bio*
.
Join me and let’s make our skate dreams come true 🤗. I’m super excited to be partnering with @trovatrip in hosting my first rollerskating retreat 🛼. But just to be clear, this retreat is open to anyone 18 years or older who is looking to connect and travel with like-minded people. Together we can decide where we go, (Japan, anyone? 🇯🇵😉) what we do (🛼🥾🧘🏼🥢🍵) and see (🌊🏔🎨🎭🌇) 
.
Fill out the survey using the link in my bio. Also if you filled it out a few months/weeks ago, and you’re still interested in going, please fill it out again! Don’t forget, you can select MULTIPLE destinations, activities, and travel time frames. After the surveys are complete we can finalize choices and book the trip! Feel free to share the link with friends and family who might want to join 🙏🏼. 
.

Thank you @energybytes for sending me some of these berry blast gummies 😋
.
Energy Bytes are meant to be a fast acting, healthier alternative to all those yellow dyed sugar-laden energy drinks. For note, 2 gummies = 1 Red Bull. Perfect for those who hate coffee and pre-work drinks. 
.
I personally love coffee, but sometimes I just don’t have the time to drink it. These gummies are fast acting with the caffeine kicking in within 10 minutes. I also love that they are vitamin enriched and vegan friendly. Vitamin B6, B12 and Niacin each support normal energy release and the reduction of tiredness and fatigue. 
.
Two of these little gummies gave me plenty of energy for this 2 hour street skate session, and got me through the rest of the day without crashing. Highly recommend 🙌🏼. 
.

Tips for doing a 180 out of a front stall. You should already be really comfortable and consistent with drop ins and stalls before attempting a rotation out. I see a lot of beginner skaters fall backwards when trying this. It’s usually due to jumping and landing in the transition off balance without staggering their feet. Turn your upper body before your lower and keep your weight shifted forward. Let me know if this is helpful and feel free to ask questions in the comments. Thanks for watching!

Hey guys! Long, personal caption alert 🚨. First, thank you. Thank you to every one of my 26.5k followers (and 7 subscribers 😅) for simply supporting my lifestyle and content. 
.
I started rollerskating in April 2019 and using filming as a way to coach myself. I decided to start sharing my progress on IG mostly as a personal blog. I also wanted to make a few new skate friends. I had already discovered a lovely community of bookish people through my other account @beccasbooksandsocks and knew I could probably find the same through skating. I had no idea skating would take over and change my life so completely. I am so thankful for this community and all of the incredible opportunities skating has given me. With that being said, this year has been filled with significant life changes.
.
 It’s been well over a month since my last post  The world has been a mess and my personal life has been full. In the past 12 months, I’ve gotten divorced, started 2 new jobs (in addition to my current 2), living completely alone (with the exception of Tunechi 🐶) for the first time in my life, and exploring the fascinating world of online dating. 
.
Skating is and will always be a part of my lifestyle, but my documentation of this lifestyle has changed. I’ve spent much more of my time at the rink than at the skatepark and more laps in the neighborhood with Tunechi than time skating the streets. But that’s okay. Life changes and I’m here for it. 
.
